        "description": "pyarrow 1.0 and 2.0 is not compatible with numpy 1.20.0\r\n\r\nRunning the following command would fail:\r\n\r\n{{pa.array(np.arange(10))}}\r\n\r\nwith error\r\n\r\n{{pyarrow.lib.ArrowTypeError: Did not pass numpy.dtype object}}\r\n\r\nNumpy release note [[link|#compatibility-notes]]]\u00a0mentions about the np.dtype related compatibility breaks. Also there is a C API change, which implies numpy dependency constraints should be tighter (whether <=1.20 or >1.20) depending on the compiled numpy version (if pyarrow is depending on it; I'm not aware of the pyarrow internal).",
