                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "There are libraries whose latest release (and even the dev branch) caps the pyarrow at <3, for example, apache-beam:\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/3d6cb85e4961585ae9c4fa3c7226916fef68998f/sdks/python/setup.py#L150]\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\nI wonder if patch releases can be made to pyarrow 1.x and 2.x to simply cap numpy < 1.20?",
